The paper focuses on software quality management in Rapid Software Development (RSD) and the development of a quality model for actionable analytics. This falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the gathering, integration, and analysis of data, which could fall under the cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category. The implementation of the Q-Rapids tool involves specifying metrics and factors, which could fall under programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the use of software analytics tools, which could fall under the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the understandability and relevance of the Q-Rapids quality model, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
